    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against required level 3 due to single-condition ASTM F1717 testing; this gap is accepted given regulatory precedent and the corroborating multi-laboratory experimental evidence. Quantitative validation results demonstrate FEA predictions within acceptance bounds (<10% relative difference, E/uval < 1.96) for all three QoIs across both laboratories. Overall credibility sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
